.two-col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0; }
.two-col > div { padding: 0 1.6rem; border-right: 1px solid #c9c0a4; }
.two-col > div:first-child { padding-left: 0; }
.two-col > div:last-child { border-right: none; padding-right: 0; }
.four-col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 0; }
.four-col > div { padding: 0 1.2rem; border-right: 1px solid #c9c0a4; }
.four-col > div:first-child { padding-left: 0; }
.four-col > div:last-child { border-right: none; padding-right: 0; }
.col-kicker { font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a6d1d; margin: 0 0 0.3rem; }
.col-head { font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.15; font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 0.4rem; color: #111; }
.col-body { font-size: 0.88rem; line-height: 1.5; color: #1f1f1f; margin: 0; }
.moves-pre { font-family: ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', Menlo, Consolas, monospace; font-size: 0.76rem; line-height: 1.55; color: #2a2a2a; background: #f5f1e6; border: 1px solid #d8cfb4; padding: 0.5rem; margin: 0.4rem 0 0; white-space: pre-wrap; max-height: 180px; overflow: auto; }
.cb-board-card { margin-top: 1.4rem; padding: 1.4rem; background: #fbf6e7; border: 1px solid #c9b67a; }
.cb-board-card .cb-kicker { font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a6d1d; margin: 0 0 0.4rem; }
.cb-board-card h3 { font-size: 1.45rem; line-height: 1.15; font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 0.4rem; color: #111; font-family: Georgia, serif; }
.cb-board-card .cb-meta { font-size: 0.78rem; color: #6a6a6a; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
.cb-board-wrap { display: grid; grid-template-columns: auto 1fr; gap: 1.4rem; align-items: start; }
.cb-board-frame { position: relative; padding: 1.4rem 1rem 1rem 1.4rem; background: #d9c89f; border: 1px solid #1a1a1a; }
.cb-board { width: 320px; height: 320px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(8, 1fr); grid-template-rows: repeat(8, 1fr); border: 2px solid #1a1a1a; }
.cb-sq { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; user-select: none; position: relative; }
.cb-sq img { width: 88%; height: 88%; display: block; }
.cb-light { background: #f0d9b5; }
.cb-dark { background: #b58863; }
.cb-files { position: absolute; left: 1.4rem; bottom: 0.2rem; right: 1rem; display: flex; justify-content: space-around; font-size: 0.72rem; color: #1a1a1a; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
.cb-ranks { position: absolute; top: 1.4rem; left: 0.2rem; bottom: 1rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column-reverse; justify-content: space-around; font-size: 0.72rem; color: #1a1a1a; }
.cb-info { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
.cb-info p { font-size: 0.94rem; line-height: 1.55; color: #1f1f1f; margin: 0 0 0.6rem; }
.cb-side-to-move { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a6d1d; margin: 0 0 0.4rem; }
.cb-solution { margin-top: 0.4rem; padding-top: 0.6rem; border-top: 1px dotted #b5ab8a; }
.cb-solution summary { cursor: pointer; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 700; color: #8a6d1d; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
.cb-solution p { font-size: 0.86rem; line-height: 1.5; color: #2a2a2a; margin: 0.4rem 0 0; }
.cb-more { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a6d1d; text-decoration: none; margin-top: 0.6rem; display: inline-block; }
.book-excerpt { margin-top: 1.4rem; padding: 1.4rem 1.6rem; background: #1a1a1a; color: #f5f1e6; border-left: 4px solid #b8902a; flex: 1 1 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
.book-excerpt .book-kicker { font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #b8902a; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
.book-excerpt h3 { font-family: Georgia, serif; font-style: italic; font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.3; font-weight: 600; margin: 0 0 0.7rem; color: #f5f1e6; }
.book-excerpt blockquote { margin: 0 0 0.8rem; padding: 0; font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.65; color: #e8dfc8; font-style: italic; flex: 1 1 auto; }
.book-excerpt blockquote p { margin: 0 0 0.7rem; }
.book-excerpt blockquote p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
.book-excerpt .book-attr { font-size: 0.74rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #b8902a; margin: 0; }
.book-excerpt .book-cta { display: inline-block; margin-top: 0.6rem; font-size: 0.74rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #b8902a; text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid #b8902a; padding-bottom: 0.1rem; align-self: flex-start; }
section.archive { margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 3px double #1a1a1a; padding-top: 1.2rem; }
.archive-title { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.1rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0; color: #111; }
.archive-intro { font-style: italic; font-size: 0.92rem; color: #555; margin: 0.2rem 0 1rem; }
.archive-list { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; columns: 2; column-gap: 2.4rem; }
.archive-item { display: block; break-inside: avoid; padding: 0.5rem 0; border-bottom: 1px dotted #b5ab8a; }
.archive-date { display: inline-block; min-width: 6rem; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: #8a6d1d; }
.archive-link { font-size: 0.92rem; color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
.foot { margin-top: 1.8rem; }
.rulebold { height: 3px; background: #1a1a1a; margin-bottom: 0.7rem; }
.foot p { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #444; text-align: center; margin: 0; }
.foot a { color: #8a6d1d; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

/* ===== MOBILE (added) ===== */
@media (max-width: 700px){
  .sheet{ padding-left:0.9rem; padding-right:0.9rem; }
  .masthead{ grid-template-columns:1fr; text-align:center; gap:0.4rem; }
  .nameplate{ font-size:clamp(2rem,11vw,3rem); }
  .sectionbar{ display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; justify-content:center; gap:0.5rem 0.9rem; }
  .sectionbar a{ font-size:0.82rem; }
  .main-grid{ grid-template-columns:1fr; }
  .story-card{ grid-template-columns:1fr; }
  .game-wrap{ grid-template-columns:1fr; }
  .two-col{ grid-template-columns:1fr; }
  .four-col{ grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; }
  .cb-board-wrap{ grid-template-columns:1fr; }
  .cb-board{ width:100%; max-width:320px; height:auto; aspect-ratio:1/1; }
  .lead-img{ height:220px; }
  .lead-img.tile .lead-glyph{ font-size:7rem; }
  .lead-img.tile .lead-tile-title{ font-size:1.6rem; }
  .lead-card h2{ font-size:1.5rem; }
  .story-card img, .game-wrap img, .origin-fig img{ width:100%; height:auto; }
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="sheet">
<div class="strip">
<span>Vol. 1 — No. 3</span>
<span>The Mind’s Gambit</span>
<span>Price: Free</span>
</div>
<header class="masthead">
<div class="mast-side"><span>{dateLine}</span><span class="mast-edition">{editionLabel}</span></div>
<div class="mast-center"><h1 class="nameplate">The Daily Gambit</h1><p class="motto">“All the chess that’s fit to print”</p></div>
<div class="mast-side mast-right"><span>Chess · Mind · Culture</span><span class="mast-edition">A Mind’s Gambit Publication</span></div>
</header>
<nav class="sectionbar">
<a href="#">Tournaments</a><a href="#">Players</a><a href="#">Openings</a><a href="#">Local</a><a href="#">Puzzles</a><a href="#">Opinion</a><a href="#">World Chess</a><a href="#" class="archive">Archive</a>
</nav>
<div class="main-grid">
<div class="col-main">
<article class="lead-card">
<div class="lead-img tile">
<span class="lead-glyph">♛</span>
<p class="lead-tile-kicker">{lead ? lead.data.tileKicker : ""}</p>
<h3 class="lead-tile-title">{lead ? lead.data.tileTitle : ""}</h3>
<p class="lead-tile-meta">{lead ? lead.data.tileMeta : ""}</p>
</div>
<p class="kicker"><span class="slot-tag">LEAD</span> {lead ? lead.data.kicker : ""}</p>
<h2>{lead ? lead.data.headline : ""} <span class="wc-badge">13 HEAD</span></h2>
<p class="meta">{lead ? formatStoryDate(lead.data.date) : ""} · By The Daily Gambit Desk · Source: {lead ? lead.data.sourceName : ""}</p>
<p class="summary">{lead ? lead.data.summary : ""} <span class="wc-badge">~55 SUMMARY</span></p>
<a class="more" href={lead ? ("/daily/" + lead.id) : "#"}>More... →</a>
</article>
<article class="story-card">
<div class="thumb tile blue">
<span class="tile-glyph">♛</span>
<p class="tile-kicker">{story2 ? story2.data.tileKicker : ""}</p>
<h4 class="tile-title">{story2 ? story2.data.tileTitle : ""}</h4>
<p class="tile-meta">{story2 ? story2.data.tileMeta : ""}</p>
</div>
<div class="body">
<p class="kicker"><span class="slot-tag">STORY 2</span> {story2 ? story2.data.kicker : ""}</p>
<h3>{story2 ? story2.data.headline : ""}</h3>
<p class="meta">{story2 ? formatStoryDate(story2.data.date) : ""} · From the Daily Gambit Desk</p>
<p class="summary">{story2 ? story2.data.summary : ""} <span class="wc-badge">~45</span></p>
<a class="more" href={story2 ? ("/daily/" + story2.id) : "#"}>More... →</a>
</div>
</article>
<article class="story-card">
<div class="thumb tile red">
<span class="tile-glyph">♞</span>
<p class="tile-kicker">{story3 ? story3.data.tileKicker : ""}</p>
<h4 class="tile-title">{story3 ? story3.data.tileTitle : ""}</h4>
<p class="tile-meta">{story3 ? story3.data.tileMeta : ""}</p>
</div>
<div class="body">
<p class="kicker"><span class="slot-tag">STORY 3</span> {story3 ? story3.data.kicker : ""}</p>
<h3>{story3 ? story3.data.headline : ""}</h3>
<p class="meta">{story3 ? formatStoryDate(story3.data.date) : ""} · From the Daily Gambit Desk</p>
<p class="summary">{story3 ? story3.data.summary : ""} <span class="wc-badge">~40</span></p>
<a class="more" href={story3 ? ("/daily/" + story3.id) : "#"}>More... →</a>
</div>
</article>
<article class="story-card">
<div class="thumb tile fide">
<span class="tile-glyph">♚</span>
<p class="tile-kicker">{story4 ? story4.data.tileKicker : ""}</p>
<h4 class="tile-title">{story4 ? story4.data.tileTitle : ""}</h4>
<p class="tile-meta">{story4 ? story4.data.tileMeta : ""}</p>
</div>
<div class="body">
<p class="kicker"><span class="slot-tag">STORY 4</span> {story4 ? story4.data.kicker : ""}</p>
<h3>{story4 ? story4.data.headline : ""}</h3>
<p class="meta">{story4 ? formatStoryDate(story4.data.date) : ""} · From the Daily Gambit Desk</p>
<p class="summary">{story4 ? story4.data.summary : ""} <span class="wc-badge">~45</span></p>
<a class="more" href={story4 ? ("/daily/" + story4.id) : "#"}>More... →</a>
</div>
</article>
<article class="story-card">
<div class="thumb tile industry">
<span class="tile-glyph">♜</span>
<p class="tile-kicker">{story5 ? story5.data.tileKicker : ""}</p>
<h4 class="tile-title">{story5 ? story5.data.tileTitle : ""}</h4>
<p class="tile-meta">{story5 ? story5.data.tileMeta : ""}</p>
</div>
<div class="body">
<p class="kicker"><span class="slot-tag">STORY 5</span> {story5 ? story5.data.kicker : ""}</p>
<h3>{story5 ? story5.data.headline : ""}</h3>
<p class="meta">{story5 ? formatStoryDate(story5.data.date) : ""} · From the Daily Gambit Desk</p>
<p class="summary">{story5 ? story5.data.summary : ""} <span class="wc-badge">~40</span></p>
<a class="more" href={story5 ? ("/daily/" + story5.id) : "#"}>More... →</a>
</div>
</article>
<article class="story-card">
<div class="thumb tile opening">
<span class="tile-glyph">♟</span>
<p class="tile-kicker">Opening Spotlight</p>
<h4 class="tile-title">{todaysOpening.opening}</h4>
<p class="tile-meta">{todaysOpening.moves}</p>
</div>
<div class="body">
<p class="kicker"><span class="slot-tag">FEATURE</span> Opening Spotlight (rotates daily)</p>
<h3>The {todaysOpening.opening}</h3>
<p class="meta">Today’s pick · {todaysOpening.moves}</p>
<p class="summary">{todaysOpening.paragraphs[0]} <span class="wc-badge">~55</span></p>
<a class="more" href="#">More... →</a>
</div>
</article>
<section class="cb-board-card" data-puzzle-card>
<p class="cb-kicker"><span class="slot-tag">FEATURE</span> Puzzle of the Day</p>
<h3 data-puzzle-title>{puzzleTitle}</h3>
<p class="cb-meta">From the Mind’s Gambit Tactics Trainer · Mate in {puzzle.mateIn}</p>
<div class="cb-board-wrap">
<div class="cb-board-frame">
<div class="cb-board" data-puzzle-board data-fen={postSetupFEN} data-moves={puzzle.moves} data-matein={String(puzzle.mateIn)}>
{puzzleCells.map((cell) => (
<div class={"cb-sq " + cell.shade} data-sq={cell.square}>{cell.piece && (<img src={cell.piece} alt={cell.alt} />)}</div>
))}
</div>
<div class="cb-files"><span>a</span><span>b</span><span>c</span><span>d</span><span>e</span><span>f</span><span>g</span><span>h</span></div>
<div class="cb-ranks"><span>1</span><span>2</span><span>3</span><span>4</span><span>5</span><span>6</span><span>7</span><span>8</span></div>
</div>
<div class="cb-info">
<p class="cb-side-to-move" data-side-to-move>{sideToMove}</p>
<p>A fresh tactic to sharpen your eye. Click a piece and find the mate — the opponent will respond until you crack it.</p>
<p class="cb-feedback" data-puzzle-feedback style="font-size:0.78rem; color:#8a6d1d; font-style:italic; margin-top:0.4rem; min-height:1.1rem;">Tap pieces to play. Wrong moves bounce back. No spoilers.</p>
<a href="/chess-school/puzzles" class="cb-more">Browse past daily puzzles →</a>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<aside class="book-excerpt">
<p class="book-kicker">From the Book · The Mind’s Gambit</p>
<h3>{todaysBookExcerpt.title}</h3>
<blockquote>
{todaysBookExcerpt.paragraphs.map((p) => (<p>{p}</p>))}
</blockquote>
<p class="book-attr">— Mourad Bouajaja, <em>The Mind’s Gambit</em> ({todaysBookExcerpt.chapter})</p>
<a class="book-cta" href="/#book">Read more from the book →</a>
</aside>
</div>
<aside class="col-side">
<div class="promo-box">
<div class="promo-img">
<img src="https://mindsgambit.com/images/book_cover75.png" alt="The Mind’s Gambit - book cover" onerror="this.style.background='linear-gradient(135deg,#b8902a,#8a6d1d)';this.alt='[ Cover loads from /public/daily/book-cover.png in production ]'"/>
</div>
<h4>The Mind’s Gambit</h4>
<p>The book by Mourad Bouajaja — Chess, Madness, and the Battle for the Mind.</p>
<span class="cta-promo">On its way</span>
</div>
<div class="side-box">
<h4 class="side-title"><span class="slot-tag">BOX 1</span> Standings · {standingsRound}</h4>
<p style="font-size:0.7rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#8a6d1d; margin:0.4rem 0 0.3rem;">Open</p>
<ul style="list-style:none; margin:0 0 0.6rem; padding:0; font-size:0.84rem;">
{standingsOpen.map((row, i) => (
<li style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; padding:0.22rem 0; border-bottom:1px dotted #b5ab8a;"><span><strong>{i + 1}.</strong> {row.player}</span><span>{row.score}</span></li>
))}
</ul>
<p style="font-size:0.7rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#8a6d1d; margin:0.6rem 0 0.3rem;">Women</p>
<ul style="list-style:none; margin:0 0 0.4rem; padding:0; font-size:0.84rem;">
{standingsWomen.map((row, i) => (
<li style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; padding:0.22rem 0; border-bottom:1px dotted #b5ab8a;"><span><strong>{i + 1}.</strong> {row.player}</span><span>{row.score}</span></li>
))}
</ul>
<p style="font-size:0.7rem; font-style:italic; color:#777; text-align:right; margin:0.3rem 0 0;">Norway Chess 2026 · After {standingsRound} of 14</p>
</div>
<div class="side-box">
<h4 class="side-title"><span class="slot-tag">BOX 2</span> Results at a Glance <span class="wc-badge">66 W</span></h4>
<p style="font-size:0.7rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#8a6d1d; margin:0.4rem 0 0.2rem;">Open · {standingsRound}</p>
<p style="font-size:0.78rem; margin:0;" set:html={resultsOpen.replace(/\n/g, "<br>")}></p>
<p style="font-size:0.7rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#8a6d1d; margin:0.6rem 0 0.2rem;">Women · {standingsRound}</p>
<p style="font-size:0.78rem; margin:0;" set:html={resultsWomen.replace(/\n/g, "<br>")}></p>
</div>
<div class="side-box">
<h4 class="side-title"><span class="slot-tag">BOX 3</span> Player Profile <span class="wc-badge">105 W</span></h4>
<p class="name">{todaysPlayer.name}</p>
<p class="name-meta">{todaysPlayer.meta}</p>
<p>{todaysPlayer.bio}</p>
<p class="cta"><a href="/daily/archive">More from the players desk →</a></p>
</div>
<div class="side-box featured">
<h4 class="side-title"><span class="slot-tag">BOX 4</span> From the Archives <span class="wc-badge">93 W</span></h4>
<div class="arch-img-ph">
<img src={todaysArchive.imageUrl || archiveSilhouette} alt={todaysArchive.imageAlt || (todaysArchive.name + " — portrait not available")} data-sil={archiveSilhouette} onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src=this.dataset.sil"/>
</div>
<p style="font-size:0.7rem; font-style:italic; color:#777; text-align:center; margin:0 0 0.25rem;">{todaysArchive.imageCaption}</p>
<p class="img-credit">Photo: <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wikimedia Commons</a> · Public domain</p>
<p class="name">{todaysArchive.name}</p>
<p class="name-meta">{todaysArchive.meta}</p>
<p>{todaysArchive.bio}</p>
<p class="cta"><a href="/daily/archive">More chess history →</a></p>
</div>
<div class="side-box featured">
<h4 class="side-title"><span class="slot-tag">BOX 5</span> {todaysWhatIs.title} <span class="wc-badge">128 W</span></h4>
<p>{todaysWhatIs.paragraph}</p>
<p class="cta"><a href={todaysWhatIs.ctaUrl}>{todaysWhatIs.ctaText}</a></p>
</div>
<div class="side-box warm" style="text-align:center;">
<p style="font-family:'Courier New',monospace; font-size:0.6rem; color:#8a6d1d; margin:0 0 0.3rem;"><span class="slot-tag">BOX 6</span> Quote of the Day <span class="wc-badge">13 W</span></p>
<p class="quote">“{todaysQuote.text}”</p>
<p class="quote-attr">{todaysQuote.author}</p>
</div>
<div class="side-box warm">
<h4 class="side-title"><span class="slot-tag">BOX 7</span> This Week in History <span class="wc-badge">85 W · 4 events</span></h4>
<ul class="timeline">
{todaysThisWeek.events.map((e) => (
<li><span class="tldate">{e.year}</span><span class="tltext">{e.text}</span></li>
))}
</ul>
</div>
</aside>
</div>
<section class="wide-section">
<div class="wide-head"><span class="pin">♞</span><h2 class="wide-title">Games of the Week</h2><span class="wide-tag">Annotated</span></div>
<p class="wide-intro">Two games worth replaying — one from the men’s game, one from the women’s — chosen for their beauty and their place in chess history.</p>
<div class="two-col">
<div>
<div class="game-wrap">
<div>
<div class="mini-board"><img src="/images/history-chess-pieces.jpg" alt="Chess pieces, close-up"/></div>
<p class="mini-caption">Chess pieces.<br>Photo: Aaaatu, CC BY-SA 4.0 — <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Chess_pieces_close_up.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wikimedia Commons</a></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class="col-kicker"><span class="slot-tag">GAME 1</span> {todaysGames.men.kicker}</p>
<h3 class="col-head">{todaysGames.men.players}</h3>
<p style="font-size:0.78rem; color:#555; margin:0 0 0.5rem;">{todaysGames.men.meta}</p>
<p class="col-body">{todaysGames.men.body}</p>
<pre class="moves-pre">{todaysGames.men.pgn}</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="game-wrap">
<div>
<div class="mini-board"><img src="/images/chess-schaken.png" alt="Schaken (chess) - Wikimedia illustration"/></div>
<p class="mini-caption">Schaken (chess).<br>Public domain (CC0) — <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Schaken.svg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wikimedia Commons</a></p>
</div>
<div>
<p class="col-kicker"><span class="slot-tag">GAME 2</span> {todaysGames.women.kicker}</p>
<h3 class="col-head">{todaysGames.women.players}</h3>
<p style="font-size:0.78rem; color:#555; margin:0 0 0.5rem;">{todaysGames.women.meta}</p>
<p class="col-body">{todaysGames.women.body}</p>
<pre class="moves-pre">{todaysGames.women.pgn}</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="wide-section">
<div class="wide-head"><span class="pin">♞</span><h2 class="wide-title">The Long Road to the 64 Squares</h2><span class="wide-tag">History</span></div>
<p class="wide-intro">Long before Morphy and Fischer, the game was born in India and carried west by Persian courts and Arab geographers. A history told from its source, not from Europe.</p>
<div class="two-col">
<div>
<figure class="origin-fig">
<div class="fig-img">
<img src="/images/history-ladies-chess.jpg" alt="Ladies playing chess - Arki School of Art, attributed to Basant Singh, c. 1930 CE"/>
</div>
<figcaption>Ladies Playing Chess. Arki School of Art, attributed to Basant Singh, c. 1930 CE. Bhuri Singh Museum, Chamba, Himachal Pradesh. Photo: SpeakingArch, CC BY-SA 4.0 — <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Ladies_playing_Chess,_Arki_School_of_Art,_attributed_to_Basant_Singh,_circa_1930_CE,_Bhuri_Singh_Museum,_Chamba,_Himachal_Pradesh.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wikimedia Commons</a>.</figcaption>
</figure>
<p class="col-kicker"><span class="slot-tag">PERM A</span> India · Chaturanga</p>
<h3 class="col-head">A Game Named for an Army</h3>
<p class="col-body">The oldest known ancestor of chess is chaturanga, played in northern India by the sixth and seventh centuries during the Gupta era. Its name is Sanskrit for “having four limbs” — the four divisions of a classical Indian army: infantry, cavalry, elephantry, and chariotry. Those four arms survive on today’s board as the pawn, the knight, the bishop, and the rook. Most historians regard chaturanga as the common root of chess, Chinese xiangqi, Japanese shogi, and Thai makruk.</p>
</div>
<div>
<figure class="origin-fig">
<div class="fig-img">
<img src="/images/history-book-chess.jpg" alt="Arab Muslims in Spain playing chess - from the Book of Chess and Dice"/>
</div>
<figcaption>Arab Muslims in Spain playing chess. Page from the Book of Chess and Dice (Libro de los Juegos), c. 1283. Public domain — <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Book_of_chess_and_dice,_page_0044R._Arab_Muslims_in_Spain.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wikimedia Commons</a>.</figcaption>
</figure>
<p class="col-kicker"><span class="slot-tag">PERM B</span> Persia &amp; Arabia · Shatranj</p>
<h3 class="col-head">The Geographer Who Wrote It Down</h3>
<p class="col-body">From India the game travelled to Sassanid Persia, where it became chatrang and entered the education of the nobility; after the Arab conquest the name softened into shatranj. Among those who recorded its story was al-Mas’udi (c. 896–956), the Baghdad-born historian called “the Herodotus of the Arabs.” It was through this Arabic and Persian world that chess crossed into Spain — not a European one.</p>
</div>
</div>
